{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Raise the rate of income tax and corporation tax to fund the NHS.",
        "additional_details": "The current crisis shows that the NHS has been underfunded for years in terms of spending on equipment and also on wages. We need a properly funded NHS to keep the country fit & healthy rather than one where we have to wait for weeks to see GPs that are under immense pressure & workload, or months to be able to get into hospital for needed operations.\r\nThe staff in the NHS are working too hard with too few resources. It's time to change that.",
        "background": "Raise the rate of income tax in all bands and also corporation tax by 2p. This should generate \u00a314bn and \u00a35bn respectively, a total of \u00a319bn. All of this additional tax be given to the NHS on top of the current budget of \u00a3134bn. Devolved governments to be given a pro-rata share.",
